    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-12-23T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-12-23T07:00:00-05:00" n="562"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d562">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/13826: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-12-23T20:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 23, 1936—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 23—11:14 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>378. Hankow’s December 23, 4 p.m. and December 20, 2 p.m. Telegrams have been
                    received today from Swenson and Fitch, American representative of Texas Company
                    in Sian, stating that Americans are safe. Sent to the Department. Repeated to
                    Hankow by mail. To Peiping, Shanghai.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
